#   # Edit .env with your values (never commit .env or any secrets)
#
# =============================================================================
# 🚨🚨🚨 CRITICAL: 2026 DESKTOP SECRET SPRAWL AUDIT — ACTION REQUIRED 🚨🚨🚨
# =============================================================================
# Multiple plaintext .txt files and folders on your Desktop (outside this repo)
# contain real production secrets:
#   - X API keys (Consumer + Access Token/Secret) in "X API/" and "X API SECRETS/"
#   - Xaman API keys + wallet seeds (fund control) in multiple "Xaman Seed and Secret",
#     "api for Xaman", "xaman api secret", "wallet created by staking platform/",
#     "quantzilla wallet seed/", "joey key/" etc.
#   - GitHub Personal Access Token in "github access token"
#   - "TextRP Security Key.txt"
#   - "WAR machine API and Secret/", "bear witness fee bot API and Secret/"
#   - Many more descriptively-named credential dumps
#
# RISK: Full account takeover on X, loss of XRP funds, repository compromise,
#       impersonation of all TextRp brands.
#
# DO THIS IMMEDIATELY:
#   1. Run:  python scripts/migrate-secrets.py --scan-all --output-proposal .env.proposed
#   2. Read the full playbook: docs/SECURITY.md
#   3. ROTATE every single key/seed at the provider (old ones are burned).
#   4. Populate ONLY FRESH values into .env (from .env.example).
#   5. Never put secrets in .txt files on Desktop again.
#
# RECOMMENDED LONG-TERM STORAGE (production & even dev):
#   - 1Password / Bitwarden (export to .env at runtime via CLI)
#   - Doppler (doppler run -- docker compose ...)
#   - Docker secrets / Swarm / Kubernetes secrets / HashiCorp Vault
#
# This .env is protected by .gitignore and .dockerignore. Only .env.example is committed.
# =============================================================================
#
# WARNINGS:
#   - NEVER commit .env, .env.local, or any file containing real keys/passwords.
#   - The default passwords below ("change-me") are ONLY for local development.
#   - For production, use strong unique secrets and consider Docker secrets or vault.
#   - Phase 1 (daily generation + dashboard) does NOT require X API keys or xAI key.
#     Those are prepared for future X posting (Phase 1+) and AI content (Phase 2+).
#   - docker-compose.yml currently uses some hardcoded values for simplicity.
#     Override by editing compose or extending with env_file + ${VAR} interpolation.
#
# =============================================================================

# --- Core / Runtime ---
ENV=development
LOG_LEVEL=INFO

# --- X / Twitter API Credentials (REQUIRED for future posting in Phase 1+) ---
# Obtain from https://developer.x.com/ (Essential Access + Elevated for posting).
# Use OAuth 1.0a User Context (Consumer Keys + Access Token + Secret).
X_API_KEY=your_consumer_key_here
X_API_KEY_SECRET=your_consumer_key_secret_here
X_ACCESS_TOKEN=your_access_token_here
X_ACCESS_TOKEN_SECRET=your_access_token_secret_here

# --- xAI / Grok API (for Phase 2+ LLM-assisted content generation) ---
XAI_API_KEY=your_xai_key_here

# --- Database (used by worker + orchestrator; postgres service in compose) ---
# Format: postgresql://USER:PASSWORD@HOST:PORT/DB
# Default matches the postgres service definition in docker-compose.yml
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://ai_stack:change-me@postgres:5432/ai_stack

# --- Redis (future caching / queues) ---
REDIS_URL=redis://redis:6379/0

# --- Internal Service URLs (consumed by gateway and worker) ---
ORCHESTRATOR_URL=http://agent-orchestrator:8001
X_TWITTER_BOT_URL=http://x-twitter-bot:8008

# --- Scheduler / Daily Posts (Phase 1 - fully functional) ---
SCHEDULER_ENABLED=true
# Comma-separated UTC times (HH:MM). Worker runs generation at these times.
DAILY_POST_TIMES=08:00,20:00
# Jitter helps posts look natural (future use when auto-posting)
POST_JITTER_SECONDS=300

# --- TextRp Community / Branding (used in post templates) ---
TEXT_RP_COMMUNITY_LINK=https://x.com/i/communities/2027587775332290785

# =============================================================================
# HIGH-RISK CATEGORIES (from Desktop audit) - Xaman, Wallets, GitHub, TextRP
# These control funds, accounts, and repo access. Use ONLY after rotation.
# Store long-term in a password manager. Derive addresses in code; never log seeds.
# =============================================================================

# --- Xaman (XRPL) API Credentials ---
# Get from Xaman developer tools / app. Separate per environment if possible.
XAMAN_API_KEY=your_xaman_api_key_here
XAMAN_API_SECRET=your_xaman_api_secret_here

# --- XRPL Wallet Seeds (EXTREMELY HIGH RISK - these control actual XRP balances) ---
# NEVER commit real seeds. Rotate immediately if they ever touched plaintext Desktop files.
# Prefer: generate fresh wallets, fund the new ones, and only store the new seeds in a vault.
# Example naming convention for multiple brands:
# XRPL_WALLET_SEED_BWTZ= sEd... or 12/24-word mnemonic
# XRPL_WALLET_SEED_QUANTZILLA=...
# XRPL_WALLET_SEED_JOEY=...
# XRPL_WALLET_SEED_STAKING=...
# XRPL_WALLET_SEED_MATRIX=...
# (Script in scripts/migrate-secrets.py will help you map the old exposed files)

# --- GitHub Personal Access Token (repo + workflow compromise risk) ---
# https://github.com/settings/tokens — use fine-grained, minimal scopes, short expiry.
GITHUB_PAT=ghp_your_new_personal_access_token_here

# --- TextRP Internal Security / Ops Keys ---
# "TextRP Security Key", internal signing tokens, etc.
TEXTRP_SECURITY_KEY=your_textRP_internal_security_key_here

# --- Other Brand / Bot Specific Secrets (from audit folders) ---
# Bear Witness fee bot, WAR machine, Matrix, Telegram bots, etc.
BEAR_WITNESS_API_KEY=...
WAR_MACHINE_XAMAN_API_KEY=...
MATRIX_BOT_TOKEN=...
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN=...

# --- Future / White-label / Security (Phase 2+) ---
# XRP_WALLET_ADDRESS=...
# ODOO_URL=...
# SECRET_KEY=super-secret-for-jwt-or-signing
# ALLOWED_HOSTS=localhost,127.0.0.1,yourdomain.com
# (Add more wallet seeds and API keys above in the dedicated sections)

# =============================================================================
